extendedInfo.directions: Microwaveable, Must be cooked thoroughly. For Food Safety and Quality: Keep frozen. Do not thaw. Microwave directions developed with 1100-watt microwave ovens. Appliances vary. Adjust cooking times as needed. Food must be cooked thoroughly to 165 degrees F. Read and follow cooking directions. Keep kids safe! Children should not operate any oven without close adult supervision. Microwave Directions: 1. Remove film. Remove chicken nuggets and sprinkles packet. 2. Microwave meal on high 1 minute. 3. Replace chicken nuggets. 4. Microwave on additional 2 minutes 15 seconds to 2 minutes 30 seconds. 5. Check that food is cooked thoroughly to 165 degrees F, careful, itÛªs hot! Let stand 2 minutes. See top panel for conventional oven instructions. 6. Top brownie with sprinkles. Enjoy. Conventional Oven: Do not prepare in toaster oven. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Remove film over chicken nuggets. Remove sprinkles packet. Cook meal on baking sheet in center of oven 28 to 30 minutes. Check that food is cooked thoroughly to 165 degrees F. Careful, itÛªs hot! Let stand 2 minutes. Top brownie with sprinkles. Enjoy. Keep kids safe! Children should not operate any oven without close adult supervision.  Keep frozen.
